    {
      "id": "node-prompt-marketplace-copy-debrand",
      "type": "prompt",
      "title": "Prompt",
      "description": "Rewrite alternate marketplace copy into a debranded but natural English listing.",
      "position": {
        "x": 930,
        "y": 240
      },
      "inputs": [
        "bundle",
        "images"
      ],
      "outputs": [
        "prompt",
        "images"
      ],
      "config": {
        "prompt": {
          "template": "You rewrite marketplace product copy into a debranded English version.\\nUse the current product fields, row context, and images as evidence.\\n\\nPreferred source English title: \"{{bundle.sourceEnglishTitle}}\"\\nPreferred source English description: \"{{bundle.sourceEnglishDescription}}\"\\nFallback product English title: \"{{bundle.productTitle}}\"\\nFallback product English description: \"{{bundle.productDescriptionEn}}\"\\nRow context JSON: {{bundle.rowContext}}\\nFull product bundle JSON: {{bundle}}\\n\\nReturn ONLY valid JSON with this exact schema:\\n{\"debrandedTitle\":\"\",\"debrandedDescription\":\"\"}\\n\\nRules:\\n1. Output language: English only.\\n2. Keep the title and description natural, readable, and marketplace-ready.\\n3. Preserve supported facts such as product type, size, material, theme, and compatibility hints when the evidence supports them.\\n4. Remove or rewrite direct branded, franchise, copyrighted, or proprietary names into neutral substitutes, abbreviations, or indirect hints.\\n5. When a short neutral abbreviation is widely legible, prefer it. Examples: Warhammer -> WH, Warhammer 40,000 -> WH 40k.\\n6. For brands such as Disney or Pokemon, hint indirectly when needed but do not output the exact protected brand name.\\n7. Do not add official, licensed, authentic, original, or trademark claims.\\n8. Do not invent characters, materials, dimensions, publishers, or lore not supported by the inputs or images.\\n9. Keep the debrandedTitle concise and title-like.\\n10. Keep the debrandedDescription aligned with the source structure when possible, but without branded names.\\n11. If the preferred row-level source fields are empty, use the fallback product English fields instead.\\n12. JSON only. No markdown, no code fences, no commentary."
        }
      },
